snippet.textDisplay:
BREAKING NEWS: Comedy Reaction Channel Gives Hot Take on Music Lawsuit.
Jokes aside, Ihave nothing against you or what you do on YouTube, but I gotta say, as a composer and producer, I disagree with the conclusion of this video. It’s in the gray area, of course, and it’s easy for a layman to say “hmmm, yeah, I think maybe it could be stolen,” just because they’re in different keys and it’s hard to approximate the difference, but I think that it’s similar enough to be considered plagiarism.

This being said, the notes themselves aren’t the most important part of this kind of thing. Did he transform the melody, assuming that Yellowcard was really his inspiration? Does the new song tell a meaningful story, or at least one that has notable differences in the affect of the melody? I’d say that he uses it in the exact same emotional context as the original. This is compounded by the fact that he also sampled Shape of my Heart by Sting in the same song only to make a hip hop version of the original with no notable differentiation between the affects of the song.

This isn’t artistic license. This isn’t a little inside joke between producers. It’s just a ripoff.

This isn’t artistic license. This isn’t a little inside joke between producers. It’s just a ripoff.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Drew, I love your videos and have been subscribed since you founded YouTube.!!
An idea for a charity would be something like Jake's Diapers or The Cloth Option. I know you're not a parent, but as many as 1 in 3 families struggles with affording diapers for their babies. I run a cloth diapering channel myself and make many videos about modern cloth diapering (Meaning modern cloth diapers aren't a big sheet of cloth and rubber pants anymore!) I help educate people how to use cloth diapers and how easy and financially life changing they are. Using cloth diapers can save families $1,500 on average, per year, per child!!
Jake's Diapers and The Cloth Option help end Diaper Need by providing families with the cloth diapers they need for their child, freeing up the money they would be spending on disposables for other bills, like rent, food and power. Many people don't realize modern cloth diapering is even a "thing", which is one reason I make the videos I do and helping families is something I feel very passionately about. With all that said, PLEASE consider Jake's Diapers or The Cloth Option as a recipient of one of your donations, now or in the future.
Thank you and keep making amazing content on your platform, YouTube. Thanks Guy!!!
